The paper deals with the capacity and storage overhead of private information retrieval (PIR) schemes, which involves information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-off between non-linear and linear schemes, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC), and the efficiency of PIR schemes, which relates to database systems (cs.DB).
